parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip out of gear, or shift unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
the transmission shifts into gear by itself
the transmission fails to engage
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power
the transmission "blew up" and needs replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates
the engine RPMs surge to a high point
the vehicle takes off without warning
the vehicle accelerates in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address recall notices can lead to critical safety issues, such as unintended acceleration, going unaddressed, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are unaware of recall notices
vehicle owners fail to take action on recall notices
critical safety issues are left unaddressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning condensate drainage system can cause water to accumulate on the passenger's side of the vehicle, potentially leading to electrical issues, corrosion, and mold growth.
symptoms: Water drips or leaks from the passenger's side of the vehicle
more pronounced when the air conditioning is on
and increases in severity when the air conditioning is off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radio's electrical system can cause the radio to malfunction, leading to a loss of entertainment and information, and potentially causing a fire hazard.
symptoms: The radio turns on and off intermittently
the radio produces smoke
and the radio may not function at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch defect and transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
a squealing noise is heard when putting the vehicle in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering is loose
there is too much play in the steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front and rear brakes need to be replaced
the rotors need to be resurfaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause the vehicle's engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The serpentine belt needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to slip, leading to loss of power and accidents.
symptoms: The torque converter needs to be replaced.
